race.comment: LAST SPLASH (8) scored by a space when a 8 length winner at this track over 600m in the best time of the card (34.86). Has a good record here including two wins. The form out of last race has been strong. Looks to have an edge on most of these. VINTAGE DUCHESS (4) was out of the placings last time but shapes well for this on her speedy win the start prior, getting around this track over 515m in 29.84. Has the ability and can find winning form again. KIWI MAKAVELI (1) looks close to another win after finishing third from Box 8 last time (30.21) at this track. Boasts a strong record from this draw with three wins and three minor placings from seven starts. Can measure up. STIPULATED (2) has a solid strike rate at this track and distance.
